title: AHS: 1984 Episode 8 Preview Breakdown! "Rest in Pieces"
author: Think Story
comment: Only 2 more episodes left! What do you think is going to happen?
Why is no one talking about Finn Wittrock possibly playing Billy Idol!
I always look forward to your breakdowns, just as much as I do the actual show.

In my opinion, 1984 is one of the better seasons. Even though it was definitely filler, I enjoyed how ep.7 gave character development to Jingles, Donna and Brooke. As long as the episodes are enjoyable I'll be happy. If you don't agree, that's fine.

They were talking (the ghosts in episode 7) about mediums going to camp redwood,that could be a nod to Sarah paulson coming in for one episode and Evan peters playing billy idol would be amazing,I don’t think this season has been the same without them,though billie lourd and Emma Roberts have done a brilliant job at keeping it afloat,love your channel,can’t wait for the next video 😀
description:
Time to breakdown and review American Horror Story's episode 8 preview "Rest in Pieces" where we look for clues, theories, and easter eggs for what the show has in store.
